item.description:
Generate key ssh-keygen -t ed25519 Write config Create a file named config inside ~/.ssh and add the following. Host &lt;server-name&gt; Hostname &lt;ip&gt; User &lt;username&gt; IdentityFile &lt;path-to-private-key&gt;
Now you can log in to your server easily with ssh &lt;server-name&gt; instead of having to type ssh -i &lt;path-to-private-key&gt; &lt;username&gt;@&lt;Hostname&gt;
Fix disconnection on idle Client will keep sending null packets every 100 seconds to keep the connection alive. Add ServerAliveInterval 100
to either
